COMMS: FLASH TRAFFIC — COMNAVSURFLANT TO ESCORT GROUP NOVEMBER.
COMMS: CONVOY NX-42 is underway from Norfolk. Two merchant vessels — MV Atlantic Conveyor and MV Nordic Ferry. Military cargo. Arrival is non-negotiable.
INTEL: SIGINT intercepted repositioning orders for at least two Akula-class boats twenty hours ago. Bearing tracks put them across the convoy's projected track. They know the route.
COMMS: The convoy cannot stop. The convoy cannot deviate. Fourteen knots on a fixed heading. They are not your asset to maneuver.
COMMS: Your escorts: USS Hayler, USS McClusky. DAGGER 03 — a P-3C from Lajes — is assigned for wide-area search.
INTEL: The P-3 is the only asset that can cover the search box ahead of the convoy. Get it out front. Find those boats before they find the merchants.
COMMS: Rules of engagement: weapons free on confirmed hostile subsurface contacts.
COMMS: COMMS out.
